        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "refactor: centralize skills subsystem",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis refactors OpenClaw skills code into a dedicated `src/skills` subsystem while preserving existing runtime behavior.\n\nThe change moves existing skill discovery, loading, runtime snapshot handling, lifecycle/install logic, remote refresh paths, upload handling, shared types, and test support out of scattered agent/gateway/infra locations. External callers now import the exact skills component they need from `src/skills/...`.\n\nBehavior is intended to remain unchanged:\n- existing `<available_skills>` prompt/catalog behavior is preserved;\n- existing skill snapshot hydration and freshness behavior is preserved;\n- preloaded skill snapshot entries are preserved;\n- empty skill filters keep their previous short-circuit behavior;\n- install, ClawHub, upload, remote, CLI, gateway, auto-reply, cron, and session paths continue calling the same underlying behavior through the centralized subsystem.\n\nThis also narrows the existing `skills/` oxlint ignore so the new `src/skills` subsystem is linted as part of core checks.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `git diff --check`\n- Testbox-through-Crabbox `tbx_01kst24t8gvspkgg0awbz2fmh2`: `pnpm test src/auto-reply/reply/session-updates.test.ts src/skills/loading/workspace-snapshot.test.ts src/agents/command/attempt-execution.test.ts src/agents/command/attempt-execution.cli.test.ts src/agents/command/attempt-execution.error-propagation.test.ts src/commands/agent.test.ts src/commands/agent.acp.test.ts`\n  - 7 test files passed\n  - 117 tests passed\n- Prior focused skills/session/CLI/gateway/cron/auto-reply validation: 49 files / 486 tests passed\n- Prior Testbox-through-Crabbox focused validation: `tbx_01kssmerwt49mvcvwk48p72qqy`\n- Auto-review completed with no accepted actionable findings\n- Manual live smoke against an OCM dev-watch env:\n  - natural weather prompt exposed and used the `weather` skill capability\n  - natural X/Twitter monitoring prompt exposed and used the `xforme-social-agent` capability\n  - both confirmed the existing skill catalog behavior is still active\n",
